Component Recipes — Custom Combinations

These recipes show how to compose existing facades into custom UI patterns. All examples work in regular tiddler wikitext — no new facade .tid files needed.

---

Recipe 1: Collapsible vtabs with detail panel

A vtabs sidebar where clicking an `act` item shows its content in a detail area:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/vtabs"
  elements="general item-a item-b item-c advanced item-d item-e"
  type-fn="[<element>match[general]then[sec]]~[<element>match[advanced]then[sec]]~[[act]]"
  state="$:/state/my/settings"
  default-collapsed="no">

  <$fill $name="view-sec">
    <strong><<element>></strong>
  </$fill>

  <$fill $name="view-act">
    &#9654; <<element>>
  </$fill>
</$transclude>

<!-- Detail panel reacting to last-click -->
<$reveal type="match" state="$:/state/my/settings:last-click" text="item-a">
Content for item A goes here.
</$reveal>
<$reveal type="match" state="$:/state/my/settings:last-click" text="item-b">
Content for item B goes here.
</$reveal>
```

---

Recipe 2: Tag editor (pills synced to tiddler field)

Use pills as a tag picker that writes directly to a tiddler's field:

```
Available tags:
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  elements="important urgent review done blocked"
  selection="multi"
  sync-tiddler="MyTiddler"
  sync-field="tags"/>

Currently set: {{MyTiddler!!tags}}
```

---

Recipe 3: Vtabs with nested pill filters (sco type)

Each section contains a pill subcomponent for filtering:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/vtabs"
  elements="colors color-pills sizes size-pills"
  type-fn="[<element>suffix[-pills]then[sco]]~[[sec]]"
  state="$:/state/my/filter-panel"
  default-collapsed="no">

  <$fill $name="view-sec">
    <strong><<element>></strong>
  </$fill>

  <$fill $name="view-sco">
    <$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
      elements={{{[<element>match[color-pills]then[red green blue yellow]else[S M L XL]]}}}
      selection="multi"
      sync-tiddler="$:/temp/my/filters"
      sync-field=<<element>>/>
  </$fill>
</$transclude>
```

Read selected filters: `{{$:/temp/my/filters!!color-pills}}` and `{{$:/temp/my/filters!!size-pills}}`

